Parliament, Tuesday, 16 June 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Home Affairs will tomorrow morning, Wednesday 17 June 2020, conduct an oversight visit to the Government Printing Works head office in Pretoria.
	
	The visit was necessitated by allegations of corruption and wrongdoing at the Government Printing Works. The allegations were made by the Public Service Union, a union which is in the majority at the entity.
	
	The committee will interact with all the stakeholders including management, employees, unions and the Department of Home Affairs with the aim of finding solutions to the challenges that are raised and to ensure that the entity functions optimally.
	
	“The committee is steadfast that it will always and with urgency address any claims of corruption. It is in this spirit of clean governance and creating an optimal and a capable state that the committee undertakes its visit to the GPW,” said Advocate Bongani Bongo, the Chairperson of the committee.
	
	Details of the visit
	Date: 17 June 2020
	Venue: GPW Head Office, Pretoria
	Time: 09:00
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON HOME AFFAIRS, ADVOCATE BONGANI BONGO
	
